<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.laiserin.com/features/issue15/feature01.php" class="external text" title="http://www.laiserin.com/features/issue15/feature01.php" rel="nofollow">Laiserin's explanation of why 'BIM' should be an industry standard-term</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.laiserin.com/features/issue19/feature01.php" class="external text" title="http://www.laiserin.com/features/issue19/feature01.php" rel="nofollow">Graphisoft on BIM</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.laiserin.com/features/bim/newforma_bim.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.laiserin.com/features/bim/newforma_bim.pdf" rel="nofollow">Building Information Modeling Two Years Later –Huge Potential, Some Success and Several Limitations</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.aecbytes.com/newsletter/2004/issue_5.html" class="external text" title="http://www.aecbytes.com/newsletter/2004/issue_5.html" rel="nofollow">Discussion</a> of the BIM <a href="/wiki/Acronym" title="Acronym" class="mw-redirect">acronym</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Building_Information_Modeling&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.buildingsmartalliance.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.buildingsmartalliance.org/" rel="nofollow">buildingSMART Alliance</a> - an organization dedicated to advancing the benefits of BIM for the lifecycle of facilities.</li>
<li><a href="http://bim.arch.gatech.edu/?id=402" class="external text" title="http://bim.arch.gatech.edu/?id=402" rel="nofollow">What is BIM?</a> - by Professor Charles M. Eastman, Director of AEC Integration Lab at Georgia Tech.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.aecbytes.com/viewpoint/2008/issue_35.html" class="external text" title="http://www.aecbytes.com/viewpoint/2008/issue_35.html" rel="nofollow">Managing BIM Technology in the Building Industry</a> - AECbytes Viewpoint #35: <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-02-12"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="02-12"><a href="/wiki/February_12" title="February 12">February 12</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a></span></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aecbytes.com" class="external text" title="http://www.aecbytes.com" rel="nofollow">AECbytes</a> - Analysis, Research and Reviews of AEC Technology</li>
<li><a href="http://bimwiki.com" class="external text" title="http://bimwiki.com" rel="nofollow">BIMwiki</a> - a platform neutral wiki forum for BIM information exchange.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.facilityinformationcouncil.org/bim/index.php" class="external text" title="http://www.facilityinformationcouncil.org/bim/index.php" rel="nofollow">Developing the US National BIM Standard</a> - BuildingSMART (NIBS)</li>
<li><a href="http://cic.nist.gov/vrml/cis2.html" class="external text" title="http://cic.nist.gov/vrml/cis2.html" rel="nofollow">CIS/2</a> - CIS/2 is the file exchange format that facilitates BIM for structural steel</li>
<li><a href="http://www.gsa.gov/bim" class="external text" title="http://www.gsa.gov/bim" rel="nofollow">GSA National BIM Program</a> - National 3D-4D BIM Program by the U.S. GSA (<a href="/wiki/General_Services_Administration" title="General Services Administration">General Services Administration</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.featurefactory.com/page.asp?pageid=122" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.featurefactory.com/page.asp?pageid=122" rel="nofollow">[2]</a> - A description of BIM or Parametric Solid Modeling on the website of Feature Factory Design Build, an architectural fabricator.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.reedconstructiondata.com/articles/read/parametric-revit-objects-part-i-fundamentals/" class="external text" title="http://www.reedconstructiondata.com/articles/read/parametric-revit-objects-part-i-fundamentals/" rel="nofollow">Overview of Parametric Objects</a> - An overview of parametric objects for BIM by Dennis Neeley, AIA</li>
<li><a href="http://www.aspenational.org" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.aspenational.org" rel="nofollow">[3]</a> - American Society of Professional Estimators</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cgarchitect.com/news/Reviews/Review055_1.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.cgarchitect.com/news/Reviews/Review055_1.asp" rel="nofollow">The IDEA BIM Architectural</a> - BIM application on top of IntelliCAD</li>
</ul>
